The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Anil brokerage debut in June

 CHANDRALEKHA TULAL

 Mumbai, Feb. 20: R Trade Securities, the retail brokerage arm of the Anil Dhirubhai Ambani Group, is expected to go on stream in June.

 Promoted by Reliance Capital, R Trade Securities will initially be set up in 50 cities across the country. Sources said the company already has 100 employees on board and is recruiting heavily to take the headcount to 400 by May.

 R Trade is headed by Sudip Bandyopadhyay, the former treasury head of ITC Limited.

 R Trade Securities has two companies within its fold ? R Trade Commodities and R Trade Financial Services. Reliance Capital is already present in mutual fund and insurance business, both life and general. 

 R Trade Securities will offer trading on both Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) and National Stock Exchange (NSE). 

 While the BSE membership is in place, the NSE membership cleared by the exchange is awaiting approval from the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi). It has got membership of the depository service provider, Central Depository Services. 

 The commodities broking firm has got memberships of the three national commodities exchanges ? National Commodities and Derivatives Exchange (NCDEX), Multi-Commodity Exchange (MCX) and National Multi-Commodity Exchange (NMCE). 

 R Trade Financial Services has registered itself with the Reserve Bank of India as a non-banking financial company. The business activities of the company is still on the sketchboard. The group will also focus on online services. 




